  "text": "Through using ≤ to compare the objective function, one can know that the interval of the objective function caused by the uncertainty has not only a small midpoint but also a small radius. Thus, the uncertain objective function can be transformed into a two-objective optimization problem. One objective optimization problem is applied to get the smallest midpoint. The other optimization problem is utilized to obtain the smallest radius [CITATION_1] .",
